          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Using Our Energy To Build Better Communities Act - Amends the Mineral Leasing Act, with respect to disposition of moneys received from oil, gas, and geothermal leases and prospecting permits on federal lands, to reduce from 40% to 20% the amount designated for the reclamation fund created under the Reclamation Act.</p> <p>Requires that another 20% of such funds be used to pay directly to each county in which mining operations occurred an amount directly proportional to the portion of such money attributable to those operations. </p> <p>Requires that moneys paid directly to such county be used by the county for its schools and roads.</p> Makes this Act inapplicable to Alaska and its counties.]]></text>
          <actionDate>2014-04-02</actionDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <updateDate>2014-04-02T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
